  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA30-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu parattaiyiṉ pirintu vanta talaivaṉ (EV: talaimakaṉ) “yāraiyum aṟiyēṉ” eṉṟāṟkut (EV: eṉṟu kūṟiyataṟkut) tōḻi colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante said to HIM who came [back] after separating from the other woman [and] who said “I do not know anybody”.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA30">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            kaṇṭaṉeṉ makiḻna kaṇṭevaṉ ceykō</l>
<l>            pāṇaṉ kaiyatu paṇpuṭaic cīṟiyāḻ</l>
<l>            yāṇar vaṇṭi ṉimmeṉa vimiru</l>
<l>            mērtaru teruvi ṉetircci nōkkiniṉ</l>
<l>            mārputalaik koṇṭa māṇiḻai makaḷir </l>
<l>            kavalē muṟṟa veytuvī ḻarippaṉi</l>
<l>            kālē muṟṟap paitaru kālaik</l>
<l>            kaṭaṉmaraṅ kaviḻnteṉak kalaṅki yuṭaṉvīḻpu</l>
<l>            palarkoḷ palakai pōla</l>
<l>            vāṅka vāṅkaniṉ ṟūṅkañar nilaiyē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>I saw, o delightful one</l>
<l rend="indent2">– and having seen [it], what can I do? –</l>
<l>the state of distress that hung over you, when you were dragged</l>
<l>to and fro,</l>
<l rend="indent2">like a plank grabbed by many, since they fell, agitated because</l>
<l rend="indent3">[their] wooden [ship] had been turned upside down in the sea,</l>
<l rend="indent">in the morning which brings suffering mixed with confusion:</l>
<l rend="indent2">a time of itching dew hotly descending,</l>
<l rend="indent2">endowed with confusion from the concern<note place="foot">The point of these two lines is, obviously, that the morning dew here consists of the tears of the 'other women' taking hold of him, but the point of the subtle structure with repeated <term xml:lang="ta">ēmuṟṟa</term> remains unclear to me.</note> of women</l>
<l rend="indent3">with glorious jewels who took your chest in possession</l>
<l rend="indent3">with a look at [their] rivals(?) in the rising(?)<note place="foot">What is here the nuance of <term xml:lang="ta">ērtaru</term>?</note> street,</l>
<l rend="indent4">where the excellent little lute in the hand of a bard</l>
<l rend="indent4">sounds sweet like the productive bee.</l>
<lg type="alternate" sameAs="10b">
    <l>the state of distress of being jostled about<note place="foot">Here another possibility of dissolving the sandhi, <term xml:lang="ta">niṉṟ’ ūṅku</term>, in which case <term xml:lang="ta">niṉṟu</term> has to be understood as a temporal adverb: for a longer period.</note>,</l>
	<l>when you were dragged to and fro,</l>

</lg>
        </lg>
         </div>
